# MindNote

**MindNote** is a prototype of a unique note-taking web application that provides an immersive experience by placing your notes in a serene, star-filled universe. It combines simple note-taking functionalities with a visually appealing background, making your ideas feel as limitless as the cosmos.

## Table of Contents

- [Features](#features)
- [Technologies Used](#technologies-used)
- [Getting Started](#getting-started)
  - [Installation](#installation)
  - [Usage](#usage)
- [Code Structure](#code-structure)
- [Future Enhancements](#future-enhancements)
- [License](#license)
- [Acknowledgments](#acknowledgments)

## Features

- **Immersive Starry Background**: Experience a calming background with slowly moving, colorful stars in light-blue, light-green, beige, and pink.
- **Add Notes**: Create new notes by clicking the plus button and entering a title and content.
- **Interactive Note Cards**:
  - **Drag and Drop**: Move your notes around the screen to organize your thoughts spatially.
  - **Expand Notes**: Double-click on a note to expand it and view the full content.
  - **Delete Notes**: Remove unwanted notes by clicking the trash can icon.
- **Persistent Storage**: Notes and their positions are saved using `localStorage`, so they remain even after closing and reopening the browser.

## Technologies Used

- **HTML5**: Structure of the application.
- **CSS3**: Styling and layout of the application.
- **JavaScript (ES6)**: Functionality and interactivity.
- **Three.js**: Rendering the 3D starry background.
- **localStorage**: Saving notes persistently in the browser.

## Getting Started

### Installation

1. **Clone the Repository**:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/mindnote.git
   ```

2. **Navigate to the Project Directory**:

   ```bash
   cd mindnote
   ```

### Usage

Since MindNote is a web-based application without any server-side components, you can run it directly in your browser.

1. **Open the Application**:

   - Locate the `index.html` file in the project directory.
   - Open it with your preferred web browser (e.g., Chrome, Firefox).

2. **Start Taking Notes**:

   - Click the **âž•** button at the bottom right to add a new note.
   - Enter the **Title** and **Content**, then click **Add Note**.
   - Your note will appear on the screen as a card.

3. **Interact with Notes**:

   - **Drag**: Click and drag the note to move it around.
   - **Expand**: Double-click the note to see the full content.
   - **Delete**: Click the trash can icon to remove the note.

## Code Structure

- **HTML (`index.html`)**: Contains the structure of the application, including the note input form and the container for notes.
- **CSS (within `<style>` tags)**: Styles the application, including the layout of notes, buttons, and the background.
- **JavaScript (within `<script>` tags)**:
  - **Initialization**:
    - Sets up the Three.js scene for the starry background.
    - Initializes event listeners for user interactions.
  - **Starry Background**:
    - Creates stars with varying colors using Three.js.
    - Animates stars to move slowly towards the viewer.
  - **Note Functionality**:
    - Adds new notes with user-provided title and content.
    - Allows dragging, expanding, and deleting notes.
    - Saves and loads notes using `localStorage` to maintain state between sessions.

## Future Enhancements

- **Keyword Linking**: Implement a feature to link keywords between different notes, visually displaying relationships.
- **Search Functionality**: Add the ability to search through notes by title or content.
- **Customization**: Allow users to customize the background or note appearance.
- **Synchronization**: Implement user accounts and server-side storage to sync notes across devices.
- **Editing Notes**: Enable editing of existing notes directly from the note card.

